olive oil
2 tbs plain flour
1 egg
1 tsp brown sugar
20 g butter
drizzle balsamic vinegar
1 packet Panko Breadcrumbs
1 sachet Nan's Special Seasoning
1 packet Pork Schnitzels
2 clove Garlic
1 packet Thyme
½ packet Tomato Sugo
1 packet Shredded Cheddar Cheese
1 Carrot
1 Apple
1 packet Mixed Salad Leaves

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced.
• In a shallow bowl, combine the plain flour and a pinch of salt. In a second shallow bowl, whisk the egg. In a third shallow bowl, combine panko breadcrumbs and Nan's special seasoning.
• Dip pork schnitzels into flour to coat, then into the egg, and finally into the breadcrumb mixture. Set aside on a plate.
• Heat a large frying pan over high heat with enough olive oil to coat the base. Cook pork schnitzels in batches, until golden and cooked through, 1-2 minutes each side. Transfer to a lined oven tray.

• Finely chop garlic. Pick thyme leaves.
• Wipe out and return frying pan to medium heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook garlic until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Stir in tomato sugo (see ingredients), the brown sugar, thyme and butter. Reduce heat to low and simmer until slightly thickened, 2-3 minutes. Season to taste.

• Top and evenly spread each piece of pork with tomato sauce, then sprinkle with shredded Cheddar cheese.
• Bake until cheese is golden, 8-10 minutes.
• Meanwhile, using a vegetable peeler, peel carrot into ribbons.
• Thinly slice apple.
• In a medium bowl, combine mixed salad leaves, carrot, apple and a drizzle of balsamic vinegar and olive oil. Season to taste.

• Slice pork.
• Divide carrot ribbon and apple salad between bowls.
• Top with Italian pork parmigiana to serve. Enjoy!